## Proposed Changes

### Backend LLM Service Layer

#### [NEW] [llm_service.py](file:///d:/ai%20powered%20pdf%20assisstant/backend/services/llm_service.py)
Create a new LLM service abstraction. This decouples our FastAPI routes and business logic from the specific LLM providers.
- Implement a `GeminiProvider` class that handles text generation and translation using the cached client.
- Implement an `LLMService` class that acts as the entry point for all route handlers.
- Future-proof the architecture for other providers (e.g., OpenAI).

---

### Backend Vector Store

#### [MODIFY] [vector_store.py](file:///d:/ai%20powered%20pdf%20assisstant/backend/services/vector_store.py)
- Implement `_embed_batch` to support embedding multiple text segments in a single Gemini API call.
- Update `upsert_chunks` to batch embedding generation (e.g., in batches of 100 chunks), instead of looping and calling the API individually per chunk.
- Export `get_genai_client` so it can be reused across services instead of recreating the GenAI client on each chat request.

---

### Backend Chat and RAG Services

#### [MODIFY] [chat_rag.py](file:///d:/ai%20powered%20pdf%20assisstant/backend/services/chat_rag.py)
- Refactor `get_answer()` to use `llm_service` instead of creating direct client instances.
- Build the conversation history using standard content objects and call `llm_service.generate()` statelessly instead of creating and destroying chat sessions for every request.

---

### FastAPI Route Handlers

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///d:/ai%20powered%20pdf%20assisstant/backend/main.py)
- Import and use `LLMService` in route handlers.
- Update the `/translate` route to call `llm_service.translate()` instead of instantiating Gemini client directly.

